HEADWORD: Salal-berry
<hw>Sal"al-ber`ry</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Probably of
American Indian origin.]</ety> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>The edible fruit
of the <spn>Gaultheria Shallon</spn>, an ericaceous shrub found from
California northwards. The berries are about the size of a common grape
and of a dark purple color.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Salam</ent>⟦br⟧
